msgid "Direction des Services Numériques/DEVeloppement"
msgstr "数字服务部/开发部"

#: _posts/2022-09-13-aphp-user-story.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The DSN/DEV  is in charge of developing and maintaining various apps and specific tools. The IT department is as vast as the APHP itself. Dealing with every single medical specialty, it is sometimes difficult to find every needed tool on the market. That’s where the DSN/DEV intervene, creating ultra specialized micro apps.\n"
"With all these heterogeneous apps, the APHP faces multiple challenges in terms of communication. Once again it is the DSN/DEV job to ensure that every single part is able to communicate properly with each other, regardless of their nature and function. In doing so their job naturally requires mastery over the data stream and the ability to manipulate it in real time."
msgstr "DSN/DEV 负责开发和维护各种应用程序和特定工具。IT 部门的规模与 APHP 本身一样庞大。由于涉及每个医疗专业，有时很难在市场上找到所有需要的工具。这时，DSN/DEV 就会介入，创建超级专业的微型应用程序。有了所有这些不同的应用程序，APHP 在通信方面面临着多重挑战。DSN/DEV 的工作再次是确保每个部件都能正确地相互通信，无论其性质和功能如何。为此，DSN/DEV 的工作自然需要掌握数据流和实时处理数据流的能力。"

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2022-09-13-aphp-user-story.adoc
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Our Chosen Technologies"
msgstr "我们选择的技术"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-09-13-aphp-user-story.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Historically a vast panel of technologies were used. In the last 10 years, our efforts were oriented toward unification. Today we are currently using only two languages : some PHP development projects for historical reasons and for the rest we are working with Java EE/Angular."
msgstr "历史上，我们使用了大量的技术。在过去的10年里，我们的努力是以统一为导向的。今天，我们目前只使用两种语言：由于历史原因，一些PHP开发项目，其余的我们正在使用Java EE/Angular。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-09-13-aphp-user-story.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "For that last part, our choices leaned toward WildFly/JBoss. We chose to package our applications in a single deliverable containing front end and back end due to the small size and to facilitate deployment. Our front end is rarely evolving, or to be more exact it evolves only when the back end is doing so. This allows our teams to quickly deploy new features. The size of our Information Network (hundreds of major apps and thousands of working instances) makes it so its global evolution is slow paced."
msgstr "对于这最后一部分，我们的选择倾向于WildFly/JBoss。我们选择将我们的应用程序打包成一个包含前端和后端的交付物，因为它体积小，便于部署。我们的前端很少进化，或者更确切地说，只有当后端在进化的时候才会进化。这使我们的团队能够快速部署新的功能。我们的信息网络的规模（几百个主要的应用程序和几千个工作实例）使得它的全球进化是慢节奏的。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-09-13-aphp-user-story.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Using containers made us revise our choices. A key point in our decision was to keep working with technologies already mastered by our teams, and thus ensuring that any deployment or development of an app wouldn’t imply a total start from scratch, but rather the use of pre-existing mods. We wanted an evolution and not a revolution."
msgstr "使用容器使我们修改了我们的选择。我们决定的一个关键点是继续使用我们团队已经掌握的技术，从而确保任何应用的部署或开发不会意味着完全从头开始，而是使用预先存在的模式。我们想要的是一种进化，而不是一场革命。"

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2022-09-13-aphp-user-story.adoc
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Quarkus"
msgstr "夸库斯"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-09-13-aphp-user-story.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The DSN/DEV kept close attention to Quarkus while researching other technologies as well. With the release 1.x of Quarkus, it became evident that it would become the tool that would take us in the right direction."
msgstr "DSN/DEV在研究其他技术的同时，也对Quarkus保持密切关注。随着Quarkus 1.x的发布，很明显它将成为带领我们走向正确方向的工具。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-09-13-aphp-user-story.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "To manage the data stream between our apps, a stream supervisor tool was created, long before we chose to work with Java EE. This tool was based on the servlet specification, and over its 10 years of existence a heavy stratification took place. As it’s still performing properly, this app was chosen as our Quarkus test subject. We could try to develop a replacement and if we encountered any unexpected obstacle we could go back to the existing app."
msgstr "为了管理我们应用程序之间的数据流，早在我们选择使用Java EE之前，就已经创建了一个流监督工具。这个工具是基于servlet规范的，在它存在的10年里，发生了严重的分层。由于它仍在正常运行，这个应用被选为我们的Quarkus测试对象。我们可以尝试开发一个替代品，如果我们遇到任何意外的障碍，我们可以回到现有的应用程序中去。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-09-13-aphp-user-story.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Our wish was to capitalize on recurring elements. From experience, our teams are able to know what can be reused and where. For a long time, we developed in a modular fashion. Each project being an assembly of mods. We are used to externalizing these mods to independent projects."
msgstr "我们的愿望是利用重复出现的元素。根据经验，我们的团队能够知道哪些东西可以重复使用，在哪里使用。在很长一段时间里，我们以模块化的方式开发。每个项目都是一个模组的集合。我们习惯于将这些mods外化为独立的项目。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-09-13-aphp-user-story.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "We rapidly managed to produce a prototype. Then a partner school was tasked to translate the two basic functions of this app from servlet to Java EE/Angular. Once it was done, we needed to go from Java EE/Angular to Quarkus/Angular. Which took only one week for one person, outside of their regular duties. Quarkus was indeed the perfect tool for the job."
msgstr "我们很快就成功地制作了一个原型。然后，一个合作学校的任务是将这个应用程序的两个基本功能从servlet翻译成Java EE/Angular。一旦完成，我们需要从Java EE/Angular到Quarkus/Angular。这只花了一个人一周的时间，在他们的正常工作之外。Quarkus的确是这项工作的完美工具。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-09-13-aphp-user-story.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Based on this experience, the project started. The supervising app was nothing more than a big mod cluster. Each mods providing its own function, it became simple to add any needed function by adding a new mod."
msgstr "基于这一经验，项目开始了。监督应用程序只不过是一个大的模块集群。每个模块都提供自己的功能，通过添加一个新的模块来增加任何需要的功能变得很简单。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-09-13-aphp-user-story.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "We were forced to overcome some limitations such as the Hibernate ORM with Panache extension preventing us from correctly accessing some of our Oracle database. But we managed quite easily to follow Quarkus evolutions and adapt our code to take these evolutions into account."
msgstr "我们被迫克服了一些限制，例如Hibernate ORM与Panache扩展使我们无法正确访问我们的一些Oracle数据库。但我们还是很容易地跟随Quarkus的发展，并调整我们的代码以考虑到这些发展。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-09-13-aphp-user-story.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Regarding Quarkus-Quinoa, which resembles our Angular approach: Because our 10-year-old packaging is still performing perfectly and totally automatized, we chose to not use Quinoa."
msgstr "关于 Quarkus-Quinoa，它类似于我们的 Angular 方法：因为我们已经使用了 10 年的包装仍在完美运行，而且完全自动化，所以我们选择不使用 Quinoa。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-09-13-aphp-user-story.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "One app is good, but the more the better. With all the experience accumulated, we created ready-to-be-used mods and methodologies. As of today we are able to fully develop and deploy an app within 2 weeks."
msgstr "一个应用程序固然好，但越多越好。凭借积累的所有经验，我们创建了随时可用的模式和方法。如今，我们能够在两周内完成一个应用程序的全面开发和部署。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-09-13-aphp-user-story.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "That experience was the result of the work of the team in charge of supervising apps. The only thing left to do was to share this experience and use it as a base for all. This was done during 2022. And to our satisfaction our Java EE/Angular team adopted this new technology without any difficulty."
msgstr "这一经验是负责监督应用程序的团队的工作成果。剩下要做的就是分享这一经验，并将其作为所有人的基础。这项工作在 2022 年期间完成。令我们满意的是，我们的 Java EE/Angular 团队毫无困难地采用了这项新技术。"

#. type: Title ==
